               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="chart">
                        <support>Textblock of straight-grained, butter-coloured
                              <material>paper</material> probably handmade in the <placeName
                              cert="high" ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7000208"
                              key="place_7000208">Indian subcontinent</placeName> with ~8 laid lines
                           per cm and no discernible chain lines, with folio <locus from="1a"
                              to="1b">1</locus> and some passages replaced, and the rest of the text
                           remargined, all in a comparatively heavy cross-grained buff-coloured
                           stock, also likely handmade in the <placeName cert="high"
                              ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7000208">Indian
                              subcontinent</placeName>.</support>
                        <extent>
                           <measure unit="folio" quantity="295">295 folios, 1 flyleaf (ff. i +
                              295)</measure>. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height>246</height>
                              <width>138</width>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
                              <height>178</height>
                              <width>78</width>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>

                        <foliation>Foliated in pencilled Arabic numerals on the upper-left corners
                           of the sides on every 10th folio starting with folio <locus>1Aa</locus>
                           rather than the opening proper.</foliation>
                        <collation> Undetermined, but probably primarily quaternions throughout.
                              <catchwords>Catchwords throughout most of the lower-left corners of
                              the b sides.</catchwords></collation>
                        <condition>Handle with caution. Text in fair condition, with extensive water
                           stains, degradation, and insect damage together with historical repairs
                           and remargining throughout.</condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="1" ruledLines="19" n="mistara">Written in 1 column with 19
                           lines per page. Ruled with a <hi rend="italic">misṭarah</hi> hand
                           guide.</layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote scope="major" script="nasta_liq" medium="ink"> Written in clear
                           <material>black</material> nasta‘līq with subheaders in
                           <material>red</material>. </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="headpiece"><label>Illumination:</label> Folio <locus from="1b"
                           to="1b">1b</locus> bears a scalloped domed headpiece with gilt palmette
                        foliate scrollwork on an ultramarine ground and an uninscribed central
                        cartouche, and four vertical radiating lines.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="marginal"><label>Ruling:</label> Folios <locus from="1b"
                           to="2a>">1b and 2a</locus> ruled in <material>gold</material> outlined
                        with thin black lines, and surrounded by another single line. The margins of
                        folios starting on <locus from="2b" to="2b">2b</locus> onwards ruled with
                        single lines of ultramarine blue.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="chart"><label>Chart:</label> Folios <locus from="194b"
                           to="195a>">194b to 195</locus> depicting the division of first through
                        fifth climes through the Persian Gulf and adjacent regions. </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="map"><label>Map:</label> Folio <locus from="199b" to="199b>"
                           >199b</locus> bears a detailed medieval style map of the world, with the
                        north depicted at the bottom of the page.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <lb/>
                     <label>Inscriptions:</label>
                     <list>
                        <item>The <locus from="Inner_front_cover" to="Inner_front_cover">right
                              pastedown</locus> bears the title and author's name in transliterated
                           Latin script.</item>
                        <item> The <locus from="ia" to="ia">right flyleaf a side (f. ia)</locus>
                           bears the Persian title, author, and brief description of the contents,
                           likely in the hand of his assistant <persName role="wst" cert="high"
                              key="person_f6587">Muhīn Dās</persName>, assistant to former owner
                              <persName key="person_f830" role="fmo" change="#role-assignment"
                              >Colonel George William Hamilton (1807-1868)</persName>. </item>
                        <item>Folio <locus from="1a" to="1a">1a</locus> bears a notation naming the
                           title and author, dated <date>5 Rabī‘ I 1233 AH (13 Jan. 1818 CE)</date>,
                           next to the numbers <q xml:lang="en">390</q> and <q xml:lang="en"
                           >392</q></item>
                     </list>
                     <label>Bookplates:</label>
                     <locus from="Inner_back_cover" to="Inner_back_cover">Left pastedown</locus>: <q
                        xml:lang="en">Bibliotheca Lindesiana</q> with pencilled shelfmark <q
                        xml:lang="en">2/K</q>, and <q xml:lang="en">Bland MSS No. <hi
                           rend="strikethrough">327</hi></q>. </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding notBefore="1775" notAfter="1838">
                        <p>Probably rebound in Delhi for former owner <persName type="supplied"
                              key="person_f830" role="fmo" change="#role-assignment">Colonel George
                              William Hamilton</persName>.</p>
                        <p>Resewn on a single flat leather thong support, with the ends adhered to
                           the first and last flyleaves. Edges trimmed, <locus from="Spine"
                              to="Spine">spine</locus> lined with cloth, then decorative
                           European-style front-bead endbands sewn at <locus from="Head" to="Head"
                              >head</locus> and <locus from="Tail" to="Tail">tail</locus> in russet
                           and white threads. Spine covered and board edges hemmed in reddish brown
                           goatskin <material>leather</material>, with squares at the edges, and
                           defined joints, but without a flap (Type III binding per Déroche). Boards
                           faced with British-made 'shell' patterned marbled paper with preominantly
                           red ochre spots and indigo veins.</p>
                        <decoNote type="binding">Octagonal <material>paper</material> label on the
                              <locus from="Spine" to="Spine">spine</locus> bears the title in
                           Persian.</decoNote>
                        <p><dimensions type="binding" unit="mm">
                              <height>259</height>
                              <width>151</width>
                              <depth>54</depth>
                           </dimensions></p>
                        <condition>Handle binding with caution. In poor condition with extensive
                           losses in the leather on the <locus from="Spine" to="Spine">spine</locus>
                           and boards, broken endbands, and loose board attachments.
                           Boxed.</condition>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
                  <sealDesc>
                     <summary>Folio <locus from="2a" to="2a">2a</locus>, upper-left corner of the
                        restored margins, bears a partial rectangular <material>black</material>
                        seal impression intaglio-carved in nasta‘līq script in two stacked lines
                        with the name of former owner or associate, <persName>Nūr Muḥammad valad-i
                           ‘Abd al-Shakūr.</persName>:</summary>
                     <seal type="stamp" subtype="rectangle">
                        <p><q>نور محمد ولد عبد الشکور</q></p>
                        <p><dimensions type="seal" unit="mm">
                              <height>11</height>
                              <width>15</width>
                              <depth/>
                           </dimensions></p>
                     </seal>
                  </sealDesc>
